entry.title: Haley Elmhorstâ€™s Story: Blazing a Trail for the Young Generation

div.p:
As a pre-teen, Haley Elmhorst fell in love with rabbits and started a YouTube channel to teach others how to care for them. After being diagnosed with a debilitating blood flow condition called POTS, she was forced to quit her job, but remained determined to start a successful online business selling rabbit care products. Today, the success of Haleyâ€™s YouTube channel has allowed her to open a brick-and-mortar store, where she sells rabbits, toys, food, and other productsâ€“ while continuing to inspire the younger generation and those with disabilities. #YouTubeImpact
Check out Haleyâ€™s channel: https://www.youtube.com/c/101rabbits

entry.title: Trenton & Heathâ€™s Story: Inspiring a New Generation of Cobblers

div.p:
Driven by a lifelong passion for footwear, brothers Trent and Heath started a YouTube channel to preserve the lost art of cobbling and revitalize their shoe repair business. Today, their business makes six times more in annual revenue than before starting their channel, and theyâ€™ve hired seven employees to help ship shoes around the worldâ€“ while inspiring other cobblers to keep the industry alive and reduce waste through shoe preservation. #YouTubeImpact
